    "We stress that this is not a restriction for what we are doing: We already know that our data are structured, in the sense that molecular structures can be (dis)similar, or belong or not belong to the same compound classes.",
    "What we are investigating is to what extent a subset of the data is a uniform subsample: If we are able to spot non-uniformness in the 2-dimensional UMAP embedding, then it is presumably not a uniform subsample in higher dimensions, either.",
